Package xgis

Class BiDimensionalMap<T>

java.lang.Object
xgis.BiDimensionalMap<T>
Type Parameters:
T - generic object to be stored in the collection.
public final class BiDimensionalMap<T> extends Object
The type Bi dimensionalMap is a data type that stores a collection of generic type in a 2 dimensional cartesian plane. This is the primary data-type we will use it to store points in our GIS.
Author:
Vinayak Mathur vxm167

  • Constructor Details

    • BiDimensionalMap

      BiDimensionalMap​(Collection<BigDecimal> xCoord, Collection<BigDecimal> yCoord)
      Instantiates a new Bi dimensional map using the given collection of x and y coordinates. A point is placed on every combination of these coordinates. The total number of points will be the product of the number of x coordinates and y coordinates.
      Parameters:
      xCoord - the collection of x coordinates.
      yCoord - the collection of y coordinates.
